1
00:00:00,049 --> 00:00:01,695
(This drama complied with production
guidelines for filming child actors,)

2
00:00:01,703 --> 00:00:03,002
(and some scenes used
generative AI technology.)

3
00:00:03,234 --> 00:00:05,966
(Episode 9)

4
00:00:25,186 --> 00:00:26,907
My father, Cha Min Ki.

5
00:00:28,102 --> 00:00:30,173
His life came to an end.

6
00:00:32,073 --> 00:00:33,875
As his daughter,

7
00:00:34,270 --> 00:00:36,302
I knew both happiness and sorrow,

8
00:00:37,850 --> 00:00:39,569
both warmth and cold.

9
00:00:44,560 --> 00:00:45,782
I buried all my resentment...

10
00:00:47,281 --> 00:00:49,474
under that tree and came back.

11
00:00:52,670 --> 00:00:54,590
- Hello.
- Hello.

12
00:00:54,595 --> 00:00:56,150
You're back.

13
00:00:56,354 --> 00:00:59,094
I haven't seen you in a few days,
but it feels much longer.

14
00:00:59,134 --> 00:01:01,186
- Yes.
- I had a family emergency,

15
00:01:01,242 --> 00:01:03,842
so I had to call off our lesson.
I'm sorry.

16
00:01:03,899 --> 00:01:05,468
Did someone pass away?

17
00:01:06,062 --> 00:01:10,160
Yes. It was a distant relative,
but I had to be there.

18
00:01:10,222 --> 00:01:12,550
- Shall we warm up?
- Yes.

19
00:01:14,574 --> 00:01:16,116
Let's begin.

20
00:01:24,280 --> 00:01:25,844
One, two.

21
00:01:35,909 --> 00:01:38,278
Sa Bin, I can't hear you.

22
00:01:42,575 --> 00:01:45,900
Don't be shy. Sing louder.
We're not professionals.

23
00:01:54,940 --> 00:01:56,633
This is driving me crazy.

24
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:08,806
- Yes.
- Well...

25
00:02:12,126 --> 00:02:13,329
Surprise!

26
00:02:14,641 --> 00:02:17,361
You seemed tired,
so here's a little sugar boost.

27
00:02:17,434 --> 00:02:18,894
Was it that obvious?

28
00:02:19,300 --> 00:02:22,610
I tried my best to hide it
and make the lesson enjoyable.

29
00:02:22,720 --> 00:02:25,938
Just as your ears can tell
whether I'm singing,

30
00:02:25,970 --> 00:02:29,726
my eyes can tell
when you're low on energy.

31
00:02:30,100 --> 00:02:31,961
I'm also good at what I do.

32
00:02:32,810 --> 00:02:35,657
Thank you. I really appreciate it.

33
00:02:36,758 --> 00:02:37,951
Another surprise!

34
00:02:38,070 --> 00:02:40,428
And this is a box of herbal tonic pills.

35
00:02:41,506 --> 00:02:44,158
You need to replenish your energy
before you're completely drained.

36
00:02:44,200 --> 00:02:47,102
Once it does, it's hard
to build your strength back up.

37
00:02:47,694 --> 00:02:51,058
This must be expensive.
I'm not sure if I should accept it.

38
00:02:51,100 --> 00:02:54,944
It's a perk of having
an Oriental medicine doctor as a student.

39
00:02:54,974 --> 00:02:58,618
My brother swears by them every morning.

40
00:03:00,218 --> 00:03:01,519
It's nice to see you smile.

41
00:03:02,920 --> 00:03:05,866
So you must live with your older brother.

42
00:03:05,938 --> 00:03:07,907
Yes. I'm still single.

43
00:03:07,928 --> 00:03:09,994
Really?

44
00:03:10,360 --> 00:03:11,781
Why are you so surprised?

45
00:03:12,870 --> 00:03:13,954
It's nothing.

46
00:03:14,020 --> 00:03:16,364
I just wasn't expecting that.

47
00:03:19,746 --> 00:03:20,866
This is delicious.

48
00:03:21,426 --> 00:03:23,446
- Thank you.
- My pleasure.

49
00:03:23,740 --> 00:03:25,897
See you at the next lesson.

50
00:03:25,922 --> 00:03:27,280
- Okay.
- Bye.

51
00:03:43,442 --> 00:03:47,243
Sa Bin, could you get me
some herbal tonic pills?

52
00:03:47,440 --> 00:03:50,536
I can't eat anything, and I feel so weak.

53
00:03:53,558 --> 00:03:54,956
Hello, Sa Bin.

54
00:03:56,218 --> 00:03:58,676
You sound even more drained
than yesterday.

55
00:03:59,740 --> 00:04:02,427
I already had some made
to suit your body type,

56
00:04:02,429 --> 00:04:04,794
and sent them to your home.

57
00:04:04,850 --> 00:04:06,332
They'll arrive this evening.

58
00:04:06,340 --> 00:04:07,772
Share them with your daughter.

59
00:04:09,214 --> 00:04:11,514
I wish I could do more for you.

60
00:04:11,800 --> 00:04:13,487
You need to keep your strength up.

61
00:04:14,630 --> 00:04:15,939
Uncle.

62
00:04:16,498 --> 00:04:18,174
Okay.

63
00:04:18,722 --> 00:04:21,556
Make sure you eat well too. Okay. Bye.

64
00:04:24,418 --> 00:04:25,884
Why are you here? What do you want?

65
00:04:26,440 --> 00:04:29,344
Why are you so cold to me?
You were so gentle just now.

66
00:04:30,630 --> 00:04:33,346
Uncle, is she someone
you're interested in?

67
00:04:33,386 --> 00:04:35,242
No, it's nothing like that.

68
00:04:35,494 --> 00:04:37,566
She's a musician I'm a fan of.

69
00:04:37,922 --> 00:04:39,306
You classical music nerd.

70
00:04:39,354 --> 00:04:41,242
You've always been such a devoted fan.

71
00:04:41,256 --> 00:04:42,894
Why did you come here?

72
00:04:42,940 --> 00:04:45,148
I can't turn my neck.
It's completely stiff.

73
00:04:46,430 --> 00:04:49,654
With that temper, no wonder
your neck is stiff. Follow me.

74
00:04:50,942 --> 00:04:52,250
What did I do?

75
00:04:57,978 --> 00:05:00,478
I haven't even put the needle in.
Stop making such a fuss.

76
00:05:03,160 --> 00:05:05,166
Treat Do Hee well.

77
00:05:05,458 --> 00:05:07,146
And don't take your temper out on her.

78
00:05:07,720 --> 00:05:09,979
- I'm treating her well.
- You say that, but...

79
00:05:10,298 --> 00:05:12,012
why is your mom so worried?

80
00:05:16,014 --> 00:05:19,616
Ma'am, have you been waiting long?
How are you feeling?

81
00:05:21,178 --> 00:05:23,093
You're friendly with everyone but me...

82
00:05:23,980 --> 00:05:27,278
- I'm a customer too.
- You there, muttering to yourself.

83
00:05:27,350 --> 00:05:28,696
I can hear everything.

84
00:05:31,258 --> 00:05:32,586
Your coffee is ready.

85
00:05:36,582 --> 00:05:37,978
Enjoy.

86
00:05:41,260 --> 00:05:42,491
I'll do it.

87
00:05:42,854 --> 00:05:45,326
What? I thought you were busy.

88
00:05:48,094 --> 00:05:50,271
We have customers. Hello.

89
00:05:50,280 --> 00:05:51,697
I'll take your order.

90
00:05:52,782 --> 00:05:54,599
- Ji Ni?
- Yes.

91
00:05:55,060 --> 00:05:56,878
I tell her everything,
even when my parents fight.

92
00:05:56,914 --> 00:05:59,284
We have no secrets between us,

93
00:05:59,730 --> 00:06:01,088
but Ji Ni...

94
00:06:01,542 --> 00:06:03,555
She didn't say a single word
all this time.

95
00:06:03,806 --> 00:06:05,352
I'm so hurt and disappointed in her.

96
00:06:05,380 --> 00:06:06,973
Is that why you can't draw?

97
00:06:07,420 --> 00:06:08,877
The deadline's in two days.

98
00:06:09,094 --> 00:06:10,991
Is it petty of me...

99
00:06:11,686 --> 00:06:13,225
to say I even feel betrayed?

100
00:06:14,636 --> 00:06:17,042
- No. I get it.
- Right?

101
00:06:17,422 --> 00:06:18,542
That girl...

102
00:06:18,580 --> 00:06:20,270
How could she hide it so thoroughly?

103
00:06:20,312 --> 00:06:23,880
If Ji Ni's life were ordinary like yours,
she would've told you everything.

104
00:06:24,580 --> 00:06:27,026
Tae O, Jung A hasn't come to the studio.

105
00:06:29,498 --> 00:06:32,357
Why are you here?
The deadline's right around the corner.

106
00:06:35,498 --> 00:06:37,278
Is that why you've been avoiding me?

107
00:06:37,314 --> 00:06:39,798
You're under pressure and can't even draw?

108
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:44,643
What if you get cut in the second round?

109
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:45,949
Then so be it.

110
00:06:46,578 --> 00:06:47,856
You know me.

111
00:06:47,860 --> 00:06:50,084
If I'm not at ease, I can't do anything.

112
00:06:50,446 --> 00:06:54,058
I can't get you out of my head.
How am I supposed to draw?

113
00:07:03,199 --> 00:07:04,780
I'm sorry.

114
00:07:05,126 --> 00:07:07,047
I couldn't tell you.

115
00:07:07,094 --> 00:07:09,270
Why? You thought I wouldn't understand?

116
00:07:11,814 --> 00:07:13,192
It's hard to admit...

117
00:07:13,702 --> 00:07:16,621
that my very existence caused...

118
00:07:17,534 --> 00:07:19,354
another family so much pain.

119
00:07:20,510 --> 00:07:24,573
They say many kids in Africa
are born with HIV.

120
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:28,858
If the parents are infected,
the child has a 100 percent chance.

121
00:07:29,938 --> 00:07:32,378
Imagine how that feels for the child.

122
00:07:32,678 --> 00:07:35,298
They're just born and breathing,
and they already have it.

123
00:07:36,040 --> 00:07:37,900
Can you imagine how that feels?

124
00:07:39,838 --> 00:07:41,085
That's how I feel.

125
00:07:44,290 --> 00:07:46,188
That's a bit of an extreme comparison.

126
00:07:47,934 --> 00:07:49,373
What's different?

127
00:07:50,086 --> 00:07:51,653
My mom and dad,

128
00:07:52,286 --> 00:07:54,466
no matter what excuses they make,

129
00:07:55,150 --> 00:07:57,550
they burdened me with this stigma.

130
00:07:59,140 --> 00:08:00,697
My so-called brother...

131
00:08:01,190 --> 00:08:04,103
dumped trash on me
and told me to get lost.

132
00:08:04,240 --> 00:08:05,260
How could he...

133
00:08:05,294 --> 00:08:07,991
I didn't want to drag you into my mess.

134
00:08:08,490 --> 00:08:09,630
Please understand.

135
00:08:13,030 --> 00:08:15,454
I'm sorry. You must've felt hurt.

136
00:08:15,456 --> 00:08:17,108
No, it's okay now.

137
00:08:18,880 --> 00:08:21,666
So you took it out on Do Hee
in middle school?

138
00:08:22,030 --> 00:08:23,543
Were you already working out then?

139
00:08:24,294 --> 00:08:28,100
I started working out
after what happened with Do Hee.

140
00:08:32,694 --> 00:08:34,310
Let's stop here for today.

141
00:08:35,444 --> 00:08:38,281
You're busy. Go draw.

142
00:08:38,320 --> 00:08:40,401
I'll give you some space.

143
00:08:41,290 --> 00:08:42,554
Okay.

144
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:45,304
I'll focus now
and not think about anything else.

145
00:08:50,225 --> 00:08:51,403
Here, you go instead.

146
00:08:51,760 --> 00:08:53,627
I don't think I'll have time.

147
00:08:55,174 --> 00:08:56,358
What is it?

148
00:08:58,818 --> 00:09:00,038
A Van Gogh exhibition?

149
00:09:01,246 --> 00:09:04,138
I tried to get a ticket,
but I was too busy.

150
00:09:04,300 --> 00:09:05,950
That's why I'm giving it to you.

151
00:09:06,040 --> 00:09:07,713
I'll let you have it.

152
00:09:10,126 --> 00:09:11,563
Thank you.

153
00:09:22,840 --> 00:09:24,186
Let's go talk somewhere.

154
00:09:25,300 --> 00:09:26,510
I've got a meeting right now.

155
00:09:27,040 --> 00:09:29,135
Wait at Tae O's café.
I'll meet you there afterward.

156
00:09:29,278 --> 00:09:30,410
Okay.

157
00:09:31,480 --> 00:09:34,100
Why didn't you answer your phone?

158
00:09:34,122 --> 00:09:35,282
I was getting acupuncture.

159
00:09:35,354 --> 00:09:37,642
- Are you hurt?
- I'm hurt because of you.

160
00:09:40,960 --> 00:09:42,318
I'm hurting more.

161
00:09:47,826 --> 00:09:50,013
Why did you only show up now?

162
00:09:50,440 --> 00:09:51,754
You're one to talk.

163
00:09:51,880 --> 00:09:53,493
Why were you born so much earlier than me?

164
00:09:55,746 --> 00:09:56,986
I know, right?

165
00:10:14,767 --> 00:10:17,183
How long do you think it'll take
before you're sure?

166
00:10:17,220 --> 00:10:19,601
- Sure about what?
- That you want to marry me.

167
00:10:20,830 --> 00:10:23,105
At least until
all four seasons have passed.

168
00:10:23,178 --> 00:10:24,511
I'm not getting any younger.

169
00:10:24,553 --> 00:10:26,220
That's why I'm in a hurry.

170
00:10:26,386 --> 00:10:27,851
I know.

171
00:10:27,853 --> 00:10:29,970
It does feel like
you're rushing because of my age.

172
00:10:30,076 --> 00:10:31,284
Don't do that.

173
00:10:31,800 --> 00:10:33,435
I still love my work.

174
00:10:33,635 --> 00:10:35,259
Don't go by my age.

175
00:10:35,261 --> 00:10:36,773
Go by yours.

176
00:10:37,428 --> 00:10:39,678
Besides, people live to 100 these days.

177
00:10:39,720 --> 00:10:42,555
Let's take it slow.

178
00:10:47,511 --> 00:10:48,720
I love you.

179
00:10:52,011 --> 00:10:54,322
I don't think I can live
without you anymore.

180
00:10:55,355 --> 00:10:56,841
What am I going to do?

181
00:10:58,011 --> 00:10:59,220
You're worrying for nothing.

182
00:11:03,428 --> 00:11:04,717
You go ahead.

183
00:11:04,761 --> 00:11:06,325
I need to organize my script first.

184
00:11:07,386 --> 00:11:08,595
Okay.

185
00:11:42,136 --> 00:11:43,345
Mom.

186
00:11:43,928 --> 00:11:45,533
I just finished my meeting.

187
00:11:46,421 --> 00:11:48,421
I'll stop by Pyeong Chang Dong on my way.

188
00:11:49,928 --> 00:11:52,747
I told you this morning
it's my mother-in-law's birthday.

189
00:11:52,803 --> 00:11:53,970
Mom...

190
00:11:55,407 --> 00:11:57,428
He'll stop by and pick up Hyeon Seo.

191
00:11:57,553 --> 00:11:59,803
Please send her
in the new outfit we bought.

192
00:12:00,470 --> 00:12:01,678
Okay.

193
00:12:26,220 --> 00:12:27,470
Na Ji Ni.

194
00:12:31,720 --> 00:12:33,011
If you'd like to order,

195
00:12:33,053 --> 00:12:34,176
use the kiosk.

196
00:12:34,178 --> 00:12:35,959
Are things so hard
that you have to do this?

197
00:12:36,970 --> 00:12:38,406
I'm filling in for Jung A.

198
00:12:39,928 --> 00:12:41,384
Whether I'm broke or rich enough...

199
00:12:41,386 --> 00:12:43,678
to fan myself with cash
is none of your business.

200
00:12:43,761 --> 00:12:45,387
You've gotten pretty tough.

201
00:12:45,908 --> 00:12:47,095
That's interesting.

202
00:12:48,886 --> 00:12:52,353
Anyway, the father you despised
is gone now too.

203
00:12:52,803 --> 00:12:54,928
That's tough.
What are you going to do now?

204
00:12:56,886 --> 00:12:58,296
Worry about yourself.

205
00:12:58,720 --> 00:13:01,626
I heard everything you did
to my mom at the funeral.

206
00:13:02,095 --> 00:13:03,746
Don't walk alone at night.

207
00:13:04,345 --> 00:13:06,845
I'll make sure you pay for your rudeness.

208
00:13:07,801 --> 00:13:10,428
It seems like you always threaten Do Hee
whenever you see her.

209
00:13:12,761 --> 00:13:13,970
Mind your own business.

210
00:13:26,011 --> 00:13:28,011
Ji Hu, she's unbelievable, right?

211
00:13:28,553 --> 00:13:31,428
But why were you looking at her
like that at the funeral?

212
00:13:31,511 --> 00:13:34,259
- Me?
- You saw Ji Ni with some child.

213
00:13:34,886 --> 00:13:36,281
Well,

214
00:13:37,053 --> 00:13:39,970
Her art is so different
from how she treats you. It's strange.

215
00:13:40,011 --> 00:13:41,663
Why do you care?

216
00:13:41,899 --> 00:13:43,702
Just think she's crazy again.

217
00:13:46,136 --> 00:13:48,861
Here. This one's on the house.

218
00:13:52,136 --> 00:13:54,323
- Hey, it's been a while.
- Yeah.

219
00:13:54,386 --> 00:13:57,761
I brought this
because it's something you like.

220
00:13:57,803 --> 00:13:58,970
Thank you.

221
00:13:59,345 --> 00:14:00,553
Enjoy.

222
00:14:01,303 --> 00:14:02,511
I'm leaving.

223
00:14:24,553 --> 00:14:26,538
Honey, coffee.

224
00:14:59,136 --> 00:15:00,511
(Death Report, Cha Min Ki)

225
00:15:03,053 --> 00:15:04,553
(Married)

226
00:15:07,803 --> 00:15:10,884
I'd like to apply for
the One-Stop Inheritance Service.

227
00:15:10,886 --> 00:15:12,053
Please submit the documents.

228
00:15:13,720 --> 00:15:15,479
The deceased was Cha Min Ki.

229
00:15:15,595 --> 00:15:16,884
I'm his eldest son.

230
00:15:16,886 --> 00:15:19,261
I brought the other family members'
documents as well.

231
00:15:21,053 --> 00:15:23,080
I never even got to wear this.

232
00:15:43,136 --> 00:15:45,886
It looks like you're
still not his legal wife.

233
00:15:46,136 --> 00:15:49,056
- What did you say, you...
- At someone else's funeral,

234
00:15:50,220 --> 00:15:52,203
please watch your behavior.

235
00:15:55,178 --> 00:15:56,691
You kept saying "my son."

236
00:15:57,428 --> 00:15:59,491
It would be nice
if I could at least give him this.

237
00:16:00,886 --> 00:16:03,312
Fine. I'll do it.

238
00:16:03,386 --> 00:16:05,005
I'll at least do this for you.

239
00:16:06,095 --> 00:16:09,011
This is my way of showing my love.

240
00:16:10,761 --> 00:16:11,761
(Senior Kim)

241
00:16:14,970 --> 00:16:16,360
Yes, sir.

242
00:16:17,123 --> 00:16:18,332
This house?

243
00:16:18,345 --> 00:16:20,514
It's jointly owned by my husband and me.

244
00:16:23,136 --> 00:16:24,537
Right.

245
00:16:24,908 --> 00:16:28,093
His share will be inherited.

246
00:16:28,636 --> 00:16:30,845
Then will this house have to be divided?

247
00:16:33,568 --> 00:16:35,245
I see.

248
00:16:35,698 --> 00:16:37,886
Thank you for letting me know.

249
00:16:38,720 --> 00:16:39,720
Yes.

250
00:16:53,697 --> 00:16:56,161
These damn documents!

251
00:16:56,261 --> 00:16:58,729
I'm seriously going to die
because of these documents.

252
00:17:02,428 --> 00:17:04,636
How did I not think of this house?

253
00:17:05,011 --> 00:17:07,613
Like a fool, I only worried about things
outside the family register.

254
00:17:08,678 --> 00:17:10,000
Seriously!

255
00:17:11,053 --> 00:17:13,053
I don't know, honey.

256
00:17:13,386 --> 00:17:14,863
What am I going to do?

257
00:17:23,345 --> 00:17:25,441
- You...
- Don't yell at me.

258
00:17:26,011 --> 00:17:28,676
And these can't be returned anymore.

259
00:17:29,261 --> 00:17:30,414
You really...

260
00:17:31,277 --> 00:17:32,301
Does Seung Hyun know too?

261
00:17:32,303 --> 00:17:35,171
He tried to stop me,
but I went ahead with it.

262
00:17:35,970 --> 00:17:38,095
He might've wanted to fulfill his role
as a father too.

263
00:17:38,136 --> 00:17:39,345
He's human too.

264
00:17:39,970 --> 00:17:42,105
O Reum's first birthday ring,
Seung Woo's wedding jewelry,

265
00:17:42,107 --> 00:17:43,759
and your gemstone ring.

266
00:17:43,761 --> 00:17:45,412
It's nothing special.

267
00:17:46,845 --> 00:17:48,011
I don't regret it.

268
00:17:49,178 --> 00:17:52,553
How much is all this worth?

269
00:17:56,636 --> 00:17:57,845
One hundred thousand dollars.

270
00:17:57,970 --> 00:17:59,178
"One hundred thousand dollars!"

271
00:18:03,511 --> 00:18:04,720
One hundred twenty thousand dollars!

272
00:18:21,678 --> 00:18:23,593
- Go back and return everything.
- Mom...

273
00:18:23,595 --> 00:18:25,886
These are people who never cared about us.

274
00:18:25,970 --> 00:18:28,011
They have even less reason to now,

275
00:18:28,053 --> 00:18:29,761
so why create this problem
all of a sudden?

276
00:18:29,845 --> 00:18:33,296
Was the wedding jewelry
I gave you not enough?

277
00:18:33,783 --> 00:18:35,116
Still, we can't do this.

278
00:18:35,136 --> 00:18:36,845
I hate that we're doing this now.

279
00:18:38,228 --> 00:18:39,801
We're okay,

280
00:18:39,803 --> 00:18:42,961
but I want help with Seung Woo's wedding
and O Reum's first birthday ring.

281
00:18:43,970 --> 00:18:46,040
- Is that too much?
- Is Seung Woo okay with this?

282
00:18:46,621 --> 00:18:48,636
After causing such a scene,
he still wants the gifts?

283
00:18:48,678 --> 00:18:49,968
Seung Woo doesn't know yet.

284
00:18:49,970 --> 00:18:51,435
You two really...

285
00:18:53,008 --> 00:18:54,461
Being smart is good,

286
00:18:54,479 --> 00:18:55,729
but don't take it too far.

287
00:18:55,970 --> 00:18:58,431
Grandfather clearly drew a line.

288
00:18:58,595 --> 00:19:00,470
This is this, and that is that.

289
00:19:00,511 --> 00:19:02,301
Don't mix them together, okay?

290
00:19:02,636 --> 00:19:03,845
Yes.

291
00:19:05,053 --> 00:19:06,261
But Mom,

292
00:19:06,697 --> 00:19:09,258
they completely emptied the bank account.

293
00:19:09,261 --> 00:19:12,163
"Empty?" You mean there's nothing left?

294
00:19:13,595 --> 00:19:16,416
What a scary world!

295
00:19:17,095 --> 00:19:18,636
But I can understand.

296
00:19:18,678 --> 00:19:20,676
"Empty?" What are you talking about?

297
00:19:20,678 --> 00:19:21,886
Before he passed away,

298
00:19:21,970 --> 00:19:23,845
I think he withdrew everything
with his debit card.

299
00:19:26,553 --> 00:19:28,094
It's not money we earned,

300
00:19:28,136 --> 00:19:29,467
so why should we care?

301
00:19:29,470 --> 00:19:30,634
Forget about it.

302
00:19:30,636 --> 00:19:31,678
Okay.

303
00:19:34,341 --> 00:19:35,384
Tell her that too.

304
00:19:35,386 --> 00:19:36,595
What else?

305
00:19:39,261 --> 00:19:42,858
She asked if I wanted the watch he wore.
She said it was expensive.

306
00:19:43,053 --> 00:19:44,053
Is she giving it to you?

307
00:19:44,286 --> 00:19:45,301
Do you want it?

308
00:19:45,303 --> 00:19:46,670
Not really.

309
00:19:47,261 --> 00:19:49,616
If I wear it, I'll think of him.

310
00:19:50,361 --> 00:19:51,384
It feels like a burden.

311
00:19:51,386 --> 00:19:52,870
Why think about him?

312
00:19:53,095 --> 00:19:54,447
It's just a watch.

313
00:19:54,845 --> 00:19:57,342
It's expensive. Take it.

314
00:19:57,553 --> 00:19:58,806
Do as you please.

315
00:20:08,049 --> 00:20:09,861
It was right in front of my face.

316
00:20:10,416 --> 00:20:13,786
I emptied the account and forgot
about this house. It drives me crazy

317
00:20:13,811 --> 00:20:16,180
Anyone would think it belonged to us.

318
00:20:16,205 --> 00:20:17,925
We've lived here for years.

319
00:20:17,950 --> 00:20:19,951
How could I not be furious?

320
00:20:20,233 --> 00:20:22,022
This anger is going to kill me.

321
00:20:22,073 --> 00:20:24,574
Can't we ask dad's company attorney?

322
00:20:24,599 --> 00:20:28,320
He thinks we're legally married.

323
00:20:29,713 --> 00:20:31,913
I spent my life covering up the truth,

324
00:20:32,086 --> 00:20:33,760
and suffered because of it.

325
00:20:34,316 --> 00:20:35,656
He must know everything by now.

326
00:20:35,880 --> 00:20:37,476
Don't start worrying already.

327
00:20:37,771 --> 00:20:41,218
The Seo Chon family said
they held the funeral because dad asked.

328
00:20:41,243 --> 00:20:42,670
Why speak of them so respectfully?

329
00:20:42,760 --> 00:20:46,792
I should've known something was wrong
when they agreed without a fuss.

330
00:20:49,513 --> 00:20:52,475
If this has to blow up,
it should be after I get you married.

331
00:20:52,744 --> 00:20:55,175
Your father never helped me with anything.

332
00:20:55,200 --> 00:20:57,812
I'm not getting married,
so stop worrying about it.

333
00:20:57,837 --> 00:20:58,959
There you go again!

334
00:20:59,326 --> 00:21:00,717
Why wouldn't you get married?

335
00:21:00,852 --> 00:21:03,908
You should have everything others have
and make an even better life.

336
00:21:04,786 --> 00:21:07,515
That damn family.
Just let them come after this house.

337
00:21:07,540 --> 00:21:10,000
I'll tear them all to pieces.

338
00:21:10,025 --> 00:21:13,065
I don't care how many documents they have.
I'll tear them all up.

339
00:21:17,193 --> 00:21:18,617
Mom!

340
00:21:19,146 --> 00:21:21,146
Money brings out the worst in people.

341
00:21:21,171 --> 00:21:22,516
Everyone changes.

342
00:21:22,593 --> 00:21:24,310
So prepare yourself.

343
00:21:35,046 --> 00:21:36,335
Yes, Counselor.

344
00:21:36,865 --> 00:21:38,795
The estate settlement's going well, right?

345
00:21:39,712 --> 00:21:40,712
Yes.

346
00:21:41,076 --> 00:21:42,509
His credit card?

347
00:21:43,273 --> 00:21:44,710
What do you mean it's overdue?

348
00:21:45,786 --> 00:21:50,637
How much could he have charged
before he died?

349
00:21:50,841 --> 00:21:51,841
What's wrong?

350
00:21:53,164 --> 00:21:54,164
Yes.

351
00:21:55,507 --> 00:21:57,071
Okay, I'll check.

352
00:22:00,605 --> 00:22:03,758
What kind of nonsense is this?

353
00:22:03,800 --> 00:22:06,045
He says your dad used the card
before he died.

354
00:22:06,420 --> 00:22:07,534
Dad?

355
00:22:07,904 --> 00:22:09,154
Did you use it?

356
00:22:09,768 --> 00:22:10,854
No.

357
00:22:10,878 --> 00:22:13,067
My heart is racing.

358
00:22:20,826 --> 00:22:21,945
Here it is.

359
00:22:26,206 --> 00:22:28,455
- My goodness.
- Is that true?

360
00:22:28,480 --> 00:22:30,267
Who used dad's credit card?

361
00:22:30,579 --> 00:22:33,299
One, ten, a hundred, a thousand...

362
00:22:33,798 --> 00:22:35,412
Hold on.

363
00:22:35,437 --> 00:22:40,550
Ten thousand, a hundred thousand,
a million, ten million...

364
00:22:41,033 --> 00:22:43,095
- A hundred thousand dollars?
- What?

365
00:22:43,241 --> 00:22:45,515
A hundred and twenty thousand dollars?

366
00:22:45,893 --> 00:22:47,970
Are those people out of their minds?

367
00:22:48,346 --> 00:22:51,602
When did they steal his card and use it?

368
00:22:51,673 --> 00:22:53,692
I paid all the funeral expenses,

369
00:22:53,694 --> 00:22:56,260
and planned to give them his watch.
Is this how they repay me?

370
00:22:56,285 --> 00:22:57,986
A hundred and twenty thousand dollars?

371
00:23:01,667 --> 00:23:02,953
Don't follow me.

372
00:23:03,193 --> 00:23:05,353
Things are going to get messy. Stay home.

373
00:23:16,373 --> 00:23:19,680
Open the door!

374
00:23:31,072 --> 00:23:34,052
That look says you know
exactly why I came storming over.

375
00:23:35,740 --> 00:23:38,104
I guess he gave it to the kids
without me knowing.

376
00:23:38,560 --> 00:23:41,417
- I was going to tell you...
- He offered it, so you just took it?

377
00:23:41,826 --> 00:23:44,226
He was on painkillers every day.

378
00:23:44,250 --> 00:23:46,380
Was he really thinking clearly
when he handed it over?

379
00:23:46,579 --> 00:23:50,091
Is this why you brought him porridge
morning and night, Yeong Ju?

380
00:23:50,233 --> 00:23:51,255
Watch what you say.

381
00:23:51,280 --> 00:23:53,865
What else do you expect me to say?

382
00:23:54,033 --> 00:23:57,837
You manipulated him while he was sick
and weak, then took his card.

383
00:23:57,861 --> 00:23:58,954
That's theft.

384
00:23:58,957 --> 00:24:02,503
- Na Se Ri!
- I paid for the funeral too. Why?

385
00:24:02,599 --> 00:24:05,483
Because he was my husband,
the man I lived with!

386
00:24:06,280 --> 00:24:09,753
This is the wealth our marriage built
over 25 years.

387
00:24:09,873 --> 00:24:13,335
Aren't you ashamed acting like this?

388
00:24:13,360 --> 00:24:17,126
- You want a ring with that money?
- It was a father's sincere intention.

389
00:24:17,300 --> 00:24:19,913
What? "Father?"

390
00:24:20,114 --> 00:24:22,427
- "Sincere?"
- He felt sorry for what he did...

391
00:24:22,474 --> 00:24:24,160
and wanted to apologize.

392
00:24:24,412 --> 00:24:26,141
You've never apologized to me,

393
00:24:26,210 --> 00:24:27,850
not even once,

394
00:24:27,893 --> 00:24:29,893
but he did, before he died.

395
00:24:30,103 --> 00:24:32,283
He said he was sorry. That he was wrong.

396
00:24:32,486 --> 00:24:34,046
I was there at his deathbed.

397
00:25:00,080 --> 00:25:01,231
Just go.

398
00:25:01,255 --> 00:25:02,491
And don't ever come back.

399
00:25:02,877 --> 00:25:05,864
Go live like your mother.

400
00:25:06,002 --> 00:25:11,479
- Go.
- Ma'am, wait!

401
00:25:11,503 --> 00:25:13,503
Ma'am!

402
00:25:27,386 --> 00:25:28,666
Please leave!

403
00:25:28,872 --> 00:25:30,199
Why are you causing a scene here?

404
00:25:30,224 --> 00:25:31,926
I told you not to come out of your room.

405
00:25:32,260 --> 00:25:33,445
This isn't your place to interfere.

406
00:25:33,470 --> 00:25:35,272
I couldn't stand it anymore.

407
00:25:35,380 --> 00:25:37,540
Mom, don't hold back!

408
00:25:37,565 --> 00:25:39,683
She's not holding back. Don't worry.

409
00:25:40,296 --> 00:25:42,589
Good, you came out. Hand it over.

410
00:25:42,666 --> 00:25:43,875
It's all my money!

411
00:25:43,972 --> 00:25:48,627
I was a fool to save his watch for you.

412
00:25:48,653 --> 00:25:51,493
Give it back now
before I press theft charges!

413
00:25:53,706 --> 00:25:56,702
I let the "theft" comment slide once.

414
00:25:57,260 --> 00:26:00,766
Someone who stole another woman's husband
has no right to say that.

415
00:26:00,985 --> 00:26:03,374
- You don't get to call me a thief!
- Yeong Ju!

416
00:26:03,399 --> 00:26:05,387
Yes, I was your senior.

417
00:26:05,412 --> 00:26:07,894
You even played the cello at my wedding,

418
00:26:07,919 --> 00:26:10,020
and then you stole my husband
and lived with him for 25 years?

419
00:26:10,074 --> 00:26:11,480
I thought it would end someday.

420
00:26:11,505 --> 00:26:13,522
I endured and waited,

421
00:26:13,546 --> 00:26:16,857
but you had a kid with him
and erased him from my children's lives!

422
00:26:17,117 --> 00:26:20,112
Who made a father and his sons fight
every time they saw each other?

423
00:26:20,136 --> 00:26:23,235
- Mom.
- He gave us jewelry as a dying apology.

424
00:26:23,320 --> 00:26:25,230
Is that really so unbearable to you?

425
00:26:25,456 --> 00:26:27,566
What? "Theft?"

426
00:26:28,053 --> 00:26:30,469
Go ahead, try it.

427
00:26:30,613 --> 00:26:32,399
Let's see who people blame.

428
00:26:32,423 --> 00:26:33,962
Fine, go ahead.

429
00:26:33,987 --> 00:26:36,062
You think I won't?

430
00:26:36,506 --> 00:26:39,342
So you're finally showing your true face.

431
00:26:39,367 --> 00:26:41,596
Acting all kind and innocent,

432
00:26:41,620 --> 00:26:44,733
while smiling like that
and driving people to ruin.

433
00:26:44,893 --> 00:26:47,200
I wonder if the world knows.

434
00:26:47,225 --> 00:26:50,789
It's all because of you that he got sick!

435
00:26:50,853 --> 00:26:52,122
Get out!

436
00:26:52,147 --> 00:26:53,988
- Do you want to be dragged out?
- Kill me if you want!

437
00:26:54,019 --> 00:26:58,696
I'm not leaving until I get my money back.

438
00:26:58,721 --> 00:27:01,542
That jewelry was bought with my money!

439
00:27:01,583 --> 00:27:03,759
It was paid for with our joint card!

440
00:27:04,246 --> 00:27:06,344
How will you prove
you were legally married?

441
00:27:06,712 --> 00:27:09,438
You don't even have a single document,
yet you emptied the account.

442
00:27:09,522 --> 00:27:12,359
You must've stood at the ATM
for hours withdrawing it all.

443
00:27:12,983 --> 00:27:15,112
That must've felt pretty pathetic
and miserable.

444
00:27:18,217 --> 00:27:19,310
What?

445
00:27:40,168 --> 00:27:43,490
(Family Register)

446
00:27:43,686 --> 00:27:45,482
Korean society is conservative.

447
00:27:45,507 --> 00:27:47,622
We should decide this
in time for the upcoming regular concert.

448
00:27:47,647 --> 00:27:49,475
The legal wife's approval is essential.

449
00:27:49,500 --> 00:27:51,598
Legally, the documented wife
has the advantage.

450
00:27:51,622 --> 00:27:52,893
Could she be a female Jekyll?

451
00:27:52,918 --> 00:27:56,891
Her art and who she really is don't match
at all, like Dr. Jekyll.

452
00:27:57,041 --> 00:27:58,084
Han Jeong Won?

453
00:27:58,109 --> 00:28:00,128
You don't know the queen of juggling
multiple guys in our department?

454
00:28:00,152 --> 00:28:02,069
- It's an affair.
- "An affair?"

455
00:28:02,093 --> 00:28:03,495
Then what about that guy?

456
00:28:05,187 --> 00:28:07,187
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
